Make sure your folder has the following files and folders:

virus_simulation_project/
│
├── app.py                ← Python file that runs your Flask web server
├── simulation.py         ← Python file with the simulation logic
├── templates/
│   └── index.html        ← Your HTML file (Flask puts HTML here)
├── static/
│   ├── styles.css        ← Your CSS (design)
│   └── script.js         ← Your JavaScript (behavior)

Step 1: Open New Terminal In VS code. In the terminal, make sure you're in your project folder.

python -m venv venv


Step 2: Activate virtual environment

venv\Scripts\activate         #For Windows
source venv/bin/activate      #For Mac

Step 3: Download modules

pip install -r requirements.txt

Step 4: 
python app.py

